   <note>Horace Maynard writing from Massachusetts mentions previous letter addressed to Brownlow in Philadelphia, "not knowing your present address." Mentions writing to Judge Trigg without receiving yet a reply. Says that the troops have left Cumberland and are marching towards the Ohio River. Mentions writing "a strong letter to the President" urging help for East Tennessee. Mentions his wife would like to hear from the Brownlow family.</note>
